get-and-set_key2: Ab aapko jo `code` humne peechle part mei samjha tha, usko modify karna hai. Usmei aap ko `get` and `set` naam ka function define karna hai class mei.
get-and-set_key4: Get as an argument ek `key` lega, aur uske corresponding value return kar dega.
get-and-set_key6: Set as an argument ek `key` aur corresponding value lega, aur usko jObject mei daal dega. Isse jab dump function call hoga, toh apne aap woh values da`tab`ase mei add ho jayengi.
get-and-set_key8: Apne dono functions ko acche se test karo, aur check karo jo values aapne set karne ke baad dump ki hai, woh da`tab`ase mei likhi jaa chuki hai.
get-and-set_key10: Jab `key` exist nahi karti toh aapka program kya return karta hai? Kya aapne `code` karte hue, iss case ko consider kiya tha?
